The Nigerian Army Corps of Military Police (NACMP) has arrested another soldier, Sergeant Thaddeus with service number 04NA/55/0931 for being in possession of illegal ammunition.SaharaReporters gathered that Thaddeus was nabbed at the gate of Maimalari Barracks, Maiduguri with about 112 rounds of 7.62mm special. “AT ABOUT 250615A MARCH 22. 04NA/55/0931 SGT THADDEUS OF 17 FIELD WAS ARRESTED AT MAIMALARI CANTONMENT MAIN GATE WITH 112 ROUNDS OF 7.62MM GOING ON PASS TO KADUNA. HE WAS TAKING TO MILITARY POLICE DUTY ROOM FOR FURTHER INFORMATION,” a military signal obtained by SaharaReporters read. This is coming a few days after a soldier identified as Momoh Sunday with service number 17NA/76/0820 was arrested at the same gate of Maimalari Barracks with about 300 rounds of 7.62mm special.